    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Valve Springs</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Clean all valve springs in a suitable solvent.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect valve springs for rust, pitting, distortion, and cracks. If any of these conditions
                exist, replace the valve spring.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2650465" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figd08/D0875.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
            <caption>Figure 150. Flatness check of valve spring</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect to verify that spring ends are flat and square to prevent lateral loads on valve
                stem. Replace any springs that do not have flat and square ends.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Measure valve spring tension using a Valve Spring Tester .</para>
            <figure id="f2650466" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd08/D0876.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 151. Measurement of valve spring free length</caption>
            </figure>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Measure valve spring free length. See Specifications .</para>
                <figure id="f2650467" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic filename="../figd08/D0877.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                             scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                    <caption>Figure 152. Measurement of valve spring free length under load</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Apply the appropriate test load to each spring and determine whether test length is
                    achieved. See Specifications .
                </para>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcsubproc>
